import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', label='mean delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='green', label='median delay = {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'].plot(kind='box')
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-',
                label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    origin_count = data.groupby('origin').count().sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    origin_count = origin_count.reset_index()
    plt.bar(origin_count['origin'], origin_count['count'])
    plt.title('Which origin airport has the most flights?')
    plt.legend(['Number of Flights'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data.index)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight dates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    df = data.groupby(['destination'])['delay'].mean().reset_index()
    df = df.sort_values(by=['delay'], ascending=False)
    plt.scatter(df['destination'], df['delay'])
    plt.axhline(y=df['delay'].max(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend(['Max delay: {:.2f}'.format(df['delay'].max())])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('Which destination airport has the most delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
